In [[telecommunication]], the term '''frequency assignment''' has the following meanings: 

'''1.'''  [[Authorization]], given by an Administration, for a [[radio station]] to use a [[radio frequency]] or radio frequency [[channel]] under specified conditions 

'''2.'''  The process of authorizing a specific frequency, group of frequencies, or frequency [[band (radio)|band]] to be used at a certain location under specified conditions, such as [[bandwidth]], [[Power (physics)|power]], [[azimuth]], [[duty cycle]], or [[modulation]].  ''Synonym'' '''radio frequency channel assignment.''' ''See'' '''[[administration]] (def. #1).'''

Source: from [[Federal Standard 1037C]] and from [[MIL-STD-188]]

